{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"crimp-polar-jag","description":"## Why\n\nWorkflow-vs-bespoke parity nit found in tepid-bus-pomp review: bespoke `pass4_coach` returns `[]` with\nNO LLM call when there are 0 surviving advisories; the workflow ALWAYS runs the `coach_notes` prompt\nstep, so a clean PASS (0 advisories) still makes one wasted coach LLM call (and a coach listing over an\nempty set). Pre-dates B5 — the coach step has always run since B2. Gate it to match bespoke.\n\n## What\n\n- Gate the workflow `coach_notes` prompt step on `surviving > 0` (a `when:` condition) so a PASS with 0\n  surviving advisories makes no coach LLM call.\n- Keep the `coach_inputs` / `coach` ops behaving correctly (empty coaching list) when skipped.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope: the `when:` gate on the `coach_notes` step in\n`src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml` (both the agentic and single-turn branches) and a test\nasserting the coach call count is 0 on a 0-surviving PASS. Out of scope: WS1 migration, WS2 model/editor,\nWS3 chunking. This story is independent of the others and can land in parallel.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The workflow `coach_notes` step is gated on `surviving > 0` (in both the agentic and single-turn\n      branches).\n- [ ] A PASS with 0 surviving advisories makes no coach LLM call; a test asserts the call count is 0.\n- [ ] A PASS/BLOCK with ≥1 surviving advisory still runs the coach step (no regression).\n- [ ] `make lint` + `make check` + the full test suite pass.\n","id":"679b-acb1-7f15-42d0","parent_id":"4e70-0cd4-0d04-4d31","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS4: Gate workflow coach_notes on surviving>0 (bespoke parity, no coach call on clean PASS)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782581466559811001,"uuid":"409753f5-4127-4f8f-b26a-4b8295d1e036"}